text.div:
AlvearieFHIRImplementationGuide

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

http://ibm.com/fhir/cdm/ImplementationGuide/alvearie.fhir.ig

Alvearie FHIR Profiles

resource.name: CDM Address
resource.description: Address wtih common extensions

resource.name: CDM Appointment
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for an appointment

resource.name: CDM Basic
resource.description: Basic is a special type of resource that doesn't correspond to a specific pre-defined HL7 concept. The CDMBasic profile extends the base FHIR Basic resource with support for additional code types.

resource.name: CDM CarePlan
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a care plan

resource.name: CDM Claim
resource.description: A provider issued list of professional services and products which have been provided, or are to be provided, to a patient which is sent to an insurer for reimbursement. The CDMClaim profile extends the base FHIR Claim resource with additional details.

resource.name: CDM Claim Drug
resource.description: The CDMClaimDrug profile extends the base CDMClaim profile with additional details that are specific to pharmacy claims

resource.name: CDM Claim Facility
resource.description: The CDMClaimFacility profile extends the base CDMClaim profile with additional details that are specific to facility claims

resource.name: CDM Claim Response
resource.description: This resource provides the adjudication details from the processing of a Claim resource. The CDMClaimResponse profile extends the base FHIR ClaimResponse resource with additional adjudication details.

resource.name: CDM Claim Response Drug
resource.description: This resource provides the adjudication details from the processing of a Claim resource. The CDMClaimResponseDrug profile extends the CDMClaimResponse resource with additional adjudication details that are specific to pharmacy claims.

resource.name: CDM Communication
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a communication

resource.name: Communication Contact Point
resource.description: Contact point extended with country and phone ext for communications

resource.name: CDM CommunicationRequest
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a communication request

resource.name: CDM Condition
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a condition

resource.name: CDM ContactPoint
resource.description: ContactPoint wtih common extensions

resource.name: CDM Coverage
resource.description: Describes the healthcare benefit coverage of a member as it relates to a health plan. Coverage determines how the health care products and services the member receives may be paid. The CDMCoverage profile extends the base FHIR Coverage resource with additional benefit coverage details.

resource.name: CDM Detected Issue
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a detected issue

resource.name: CDM Eligibility
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for an eligibility record

resource.name: CDM Encounter
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for an encounter

resource.name: CDM Explanation of Benefit
resource.description: This resource provides: the claim details; adjudication details from the processing of a Claim; and optionally account balance information, for informing the subscriber of the benefits provided. The CDMExplanationOfBenefit profile extends the base FHIR ExplanationOfBenefit resource with additional details.

resource.name: CDM Explanation of Benefit for Analytics
resource.description: The CDMExplanationOfBenefitForAnalytics profile extends the base CDMExplanationOfBenefit profile with additional details that are useful for analytics.

resource.name: CDM Identifier
resource.description: CDM identifier with extensions

resource.name: CDM Insurance Plan
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for an insurance plan

resource.name: CDM Library
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a library

resource.name: CDM Location
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a location

resource.name: Location Matching - Match Location
resource.description: Match location record created when matched locations are found, containing links to the source location resources that were matched

resource.name: CDM Match Patient
resource.description: Match patient record created when matched patients are found, containing links to the source patient resources that were matched

resource.name: CDM Match Practitioner
resource.description: Match practitioner record created when matched practitioners are found, containing links to the source practitioner resources that were matched

resource.name: CDM Observation
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for an observation

resource.name: CDM Organization
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a organization

resource.name: CDM Organization Affiliation
resource.description: Health Data Connect organization affiliation with versioned hierarchy levels used to relate parent and child organizations

resource.name: CDM Patient
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a patient

resource.name: CDM Person
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a person

resource.name: CDM Practitioner
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a practitioner

resource.name: CDM Practitioner Bundle
resource.description: Health Data Connect bundle used to package Common Data Model practitioner resources for data ingestion

resource.name: CDM Practitioner Role
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a practitioner role

resource.name: CDM Procedure
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for a procedure

resource.name: CDM Service Request
resource.description: A record of a request for service such as diagnostic investigations, treatments, or operations to be performed. The CDMServiceRequest profile extends the base FHIR ServiceRequest resource with additional details.

resource.name: Care Gap Detected Issue
resource.description: Detected issues to record a history of open and closed care gaps identified for a patient over time.

resource.name: Engagement Communication
resource.description: This profile is a record of an engagement communication to a patient including successful, planned, and failed communications.

resource.name: Engagement CommunicationRequest
resource.description: This profile is a record of an engagement request for a communication to a patient.

resource.name: Fee for Value Initative
resource.description: Health Data Connect Common Data Model definition of what fields we currently define for an FFV initiative record

resource.name: Hierarchy Practitioner Role
resource.description: Practitioner role used to represent a hierarchy within an organization

resource.name: Measure Population Observation
resource.description: Observation created by Health Data Connect to record measure populations for a patient over time

resource.name: ParameterDefinition With Default
resource.description: ParameterDefinition with optional detailt value

resource.name: ParameterDefinition With Value
resource.description: ParameterDefinition with the parameter value that was used

resource.name: Patient List
resource.description: A list of references to specific patients

resource.name: Practitioner List
resource.description: A list of references to specific practitioners

resource.name: Process Meta
resource.description: Data lineage meta with process extensions

resource.name: Quality Measure
resource.description: The quality measure profile is limited to measures with proportion and ratio scoring methods. The profile requires an initial population, denominator, and numerator in accordance with FHIR quality reporting guidelines. Measure population and measure population exclusions are not allowed.  The profile also supports care gap populations for additional use cases.

resource.name: Quality Measure List
resource.description: A list of references to specific measures

resource.name: Organization Quality Measure Report
resource.description: A quality measure report with an organizational focus

resource.name: Patient Quality Measure Report
resource.description: A quality measure report focused on a single patient

resource.name: Practitioner Quality Measure Report
resource.description: A quality measure report focused on practitioner performance

resource.name: Quality Measure Report
resource.description: An abstract quality measure report profile. This profile serves as the base for organizational, practitioner, and patient-focused quality measure reports.

resource.name: Quantity With Conversion
resource.description: Quantity with converted quanitity for standard unit values

resource.name: Reference With Code and Period
resource.description: A reference with one or more contextual codes and an optional period defining the time period in which the reference is valid

resource.name: Reference With Period
resource.description: A reference with a period defining the time period in which the reference is valid

resource.name: Reference With Sequence
resource.description: A reference with an optional sequence defining the order in which the reference is considered

resource.name: ACA Health Insurance Oversight System Plan
resource.description: Code for Affordable Care Act (ACA) HIOS plan. The value is the combination of HIOS Issuer ID, Product ID, Component ID, and Cost Sharing Variant.

resource.name: ACA Health Insurance Oversight System Product
resource.description: Code for Affordable Care Act (ACA) HIOS product ID and component code of the associated plan

resource.name: ACA Market Type
resource.description: Code for Affordable Care Act (ACA) market type of the associated plan

resource.name: ACA Metal Tier
resource.description: Code for Affordable Care Act (ACA) metal tier of the associated plan

resource.name: Adjudication Date
resource.description: Date on which the payment status of the claim was adjudicated

resource.name: Admit Count
resource.description: Used to determine which facility claims should be counted as inpatient admissions

resource.name: Age and Gender Groups
resource.description: Standard code for groupings that combine age and gender

resource.name: Age Group
resource.description: Standard code for age groupings

resource.name: Aggregate Claim Indicator
resource.description: Indicates whether this claim record is included in the adjustment processing of the aggregate build logic for admissions, episodes or DCGs

resource.name: Allowed Amount Inpatient (USD)
resource.description: Allowed amount for an in-patient, in USD

resource.name: Allowed Amount Managing Physician (USD)
resource.description: Allowed amount for the managing physician, in USD

resource.name: Assigned Practitioner
resource.description: The practitioner assigned to the patient

resource.name: Attributed Provider Reference with Period
resource.description: A reference to an attributed practitioner resource with a period defining the time period in which the attribution is valid

resource.name: Attribution Code
resource.description: FFV initiative attribution method code

resource.name: Average Wholesale Price
resource.description: The average wholesale price charged by wholesalers for the specific drug

resource.name: Benefit Status
resource.description: HIPAA standard code for the benefit status

resource.name: CanonicalMeasure
resource.description: Canonical reference to the specific version of the measure used to generate the resource.

resource.name: Capitated Service Indicator
resource.description: Indicates whether this service (encounter record) was capitated

resource.name: Capitation Arrangement
resource.description: Code for the capitation arrangement

resource.name: CareGapComplianceEventDisplayName
resource.description: Text describing the treatment or compliance event required to close the care gap.  Should be suitable for display to patient.

resource.name: CareGapComplianceFrequency
resource.description: Text describing the frequency of the treatment or compliance event required to close the care gap.  Frequency should be suitable for display to patient.

resource.name: CareGapComplianceMet
resource.description: Indicates if the patient received the targeted treatment to close the care gap.

resource.name: Carve Out
resource.description: Code for the carveout group

resource.name: Category
resource.description: Top level category for classification purposes

resource.name: Child Organization Hierarchy Level Description
resource.description: Description of the level of the child practitioner within the organinzational hierarchy

resource.name: Child Organization Hierarchy Level Code
resource.description: Numeric level of the child practitioner within the organinzational hierarchy

resource.name: Citizen Status
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the citizenship status of the person

resource.name: Claim Adjustment Type
resource.description: The code for the claim's adjustment type

resource.name: Claim Category
resource.description: Standard HIPAA code for the category of the claim status

resource.name: Claim Group Identifier
resource.description: Group ID of the plan member. This ID associates the primary plan holder with any dependents.

resource.name: Claim Item Detail Classification
resource.description: Classification of the information contained in this claim item detail section

resource.name: Claim Received Date
resource.description: Date the claim was received

resource.name: Claim Response Benefit Plan
resource.description: The benefit plan on the claim item

resource.name: Claim Response Item Status
resource.description: Payment status of claim item

resource.name: Claim Snapshot Provider Name
resource.description: Original provider name as reported on the claim

resource.name: Claim Snapshot Provider Zip Code
resource.description: Original provider postal code, as reported on the claim

resource.name: Claim Status
resource.description: Code for the status of a claim

resource.name: Claim Type
resource.description: Type of claim determined from the clinical source and not adjudicated claim

resource.name: Cobra Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act(COBRA) continuation for the person

resource.name: Communication Care Gap
resource.description: ID of care gap for which we are communicating

resource.name: Communication Contact
resource.description: Phone number, email, or address to contact

resource.name: Communication Language
resource.description: Language used for communication messaging content

resource.name: Communication Measure
resource.description: Reference to the measure that resulted in the communication

resource.name: Communication Mode
resource.description: Mode of communication (phone | sms | email | mail | chat)

resource.name: Communication On-Behalf Of
resource.description: Attributed provider, location, or organization communication is on-behalf of

resource.name: Communication Opt-Out
resource.description: Opt-out patient for communications by product and/or mode

resource.name: Communication Outcome
resource.description: Vendor-specific communication response code or text

resource.name: Communication Payload Data
resource.description: Contains dynamic data elements and vendor / medium specific elements to be included in the message payload

resource.name: Communication Priority Sequence
resource.description: Priority of the communication request (1 = highest)

resource.name: Communication Product
resource.description: Product generating the communication

resource.name: Communication Reengagement
resource.description: Sequence for subsequent communication attempts to reengage the patient

resource.name: Communication Retry Limit
resource.description: Retry limit configuration, may vary by medium and vendor

resource.name: Communication Sent Time
resource.description: Time communication was attempted

resource.name: Communication Template
resource.description: ID or url reference to template to be used for communication

resource.name: Communication Vendor
resource.description: Vendor used to send the communication

resource.name: Company Code
resource.description: Company code of the subscriber as reported on the claim

resource.name: Compound Code
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the compound of the drug

resource.name: Condition Disease Course
resource.description: Clinical course of the disease (how the disease behaves over time), such as acute versus chronic

resource.name: Conversation Type
resource.description: Type of conversation, used for chat communications

resource.name: Converted Quantity
resource.description: Converted quantity expressed in standard unit value

resource.name: Copay Exclusion
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the exclusion reason of a copayment

resource.name: Cost Sharing Reduction Variant
resource.description: Code for Affordable Care Act (ACA) cost sharing reduction variant of the associated plan

resource.name: County Code
resource.description: The county code for the address

resource.name: Coverage Days
resource.description: Number of covered days of eligibility

resource.name: Coverage Insurance Plan
resource.description: Reference to the insurance plan for this coverage

resource.name: Coverage Month
resource.description: Date which reflects the month of eligibility

resource.name: Covered Text
resource.description: Snippet of covered text used as input to the insight asseessment

resource.name: Crossover Indicator
resource.description: Indicates whether the claim is a crossover claim where a portion is paid by Medicare

resource.name: Days To Process
resource.description: Number of days between the date the claim was received and the date the claim was processed

resource.name: Default Value
resource.description: Default value for the parameter

resource.name: Dental Fully Insured Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of the fully insured dental coverage for the member or employee

resource.name: Description
resource.description: Plain text description that explains the insight score result

resource.name: Detected
resource.description: When the insight evaluation occurred.

resource.name: Disposition Reason
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the disposition reason, as related to how the claim was paid

resource.name: Documented Sex
resource.description: Sex coding indicated on the legal document

resource.name: Documented Source
resource.description: Source type of the legal document

resource.name: Documented System
resource.description: Source system or jurisdiction of the legal document

resource.name: Drug Fully Insured Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of the fully insured drug coverage for the member or employee

resource.name: Dual Eligibility Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of dual eligibility for the Medicaid market

resource.name: Effective Period
resource.description: Effective period

resource.name: Element Source Classification
resource.description: Classification of the origin of the data value associated to a given element in a FHIR resource. The intent is that this extension value should be populated with a code from the process-meta-source-classification valueset.

resource.name: Employee Average Scheduled Hours
resource.description: Average number of hours the employee is scheduled to work per day

resource.name: Employee Birth Date
resource.description: Birthdate of the employee or contract holder. For security, this field may be hidden or the value stored in this field should only contain the year

resource.name: Employee Business Unit
resource.description: Business unit of the subscriber as reported on the claim

resource.name: Employee Company
resource.description: Code for the company of the employee

resource.name: Employee Cost Center
resource.description: Code for the cost center of the employee

resource.name: Employee Count
resource.description: Flag of the employees in the eligibility record. Each employee is identified with a value of 1. All others are given values of 0.

resource.name: Employee Department
resource.description: Code for the department of the employee

resource.name: Employee Division
resource.description: Code for the division of the employee

resource.name: Employee Education Level
resource.description: Code indicating the highest level of education that the employee has completed (e.g., not a high school graduate, high school graduate, some college, associates degree, bachelors degree, graduate degree)

resource.name: Employee Exempt Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of whether the employee status is exempt or non-exempt

resource.name: Employee FTE Count
resource.description: Full Time Equivalent calculation for the employee. Example 1: A full-time employee would have a value of 1. Example 2: A 20-hour per week employee would have a value of 0.5.

resource.name: Employee Family Size
resource.description: Total family size of the employee, whether or not dependents are insured or participating in any programs

resource.name: Employee Gender
resource.description: Employee gender code

resource.name: Employee Hire Date
resource.description: First date of employment for the employee

resource.name: Employee Id
resource.description: Identifier for the employee

resource.name: Employee Job Family
resource.description: Code for the job family of the employee

resource.name: Employee Job Grade
resource.description: Code for the job grade of the employee

resource.name: Employee Job Location
resource.description: Code for the physical location where the employee works

resource.name: Employee Job Title
resource.description: Job title of the employee

resource.name: Employee Labor Union
resource.description: Code for the labor union of the employee

resource.name: Employee Pay Frequency
resource.description: Code indicating the frequency with which the employee is paid (e.g., daily, weekly, monthly)

resource.name: Employee Performance Rating
resource.description: Code indicating the performance rating of the employee, assigned as of the last review period

resource.name: Employee Retirement Date
resource.description: Date of retirement for the employee or contract holder

resource.name: Employee Shift
resource.description: Code indicating the regular shift which the employee is scheduled to work (e.g., day, afternoon, midnight)

resource.name: Employee Age In Years
resource.description: Age in years at the time of the event for the employee

resource.name: Employee Status
resource.description: Status of the employee based on one or more code systems. Example codes include HIPAA (HipaaEmployeeStatusCodeSystem), Payer (WhPayerEmployeeStatusCodeSystem) or customer-specific codes.

resource.name: Employee Sub Business Unit
resource.description: Code of the sub business unit of the employee

resource.name: Employee Termination Date
resource.description: Last date of employment for the employee

resource.name: Employee Termination Reason
resource.description: Code indicating the reason for employee termination, if the employee was terminated (e.g., discharged, resigned)

resource.name: Employee Union Id
resource.description: Identification for the labor union member

resource.name: Employee Wage Amount
resource.description: Wage amount of the employee for the time period represented by the Wage Basis field

resource.name: Employee Wage Basis
resource.description: Code indicating the basis on which the wages of the employee are calculated (e.g., hourly, daily, weekly, bimonthly, monthly, annually)

resource.name: Employee Year Of Service
resource.description: Net credited service in years for the employee

resource.name: Employer
resource.description: Code for the employer as reported on the claim record

resource.name: Encrypted State
resource.description: Encrypted state

resource.name: Enrollment PCP
resource.description: Provider identifier of the primary care physician for the plan member

resource.name: Enrollment PCP Name On Enrollment
resource.description: Original primary care physician (PCP) name as reporting on the eligibility record

resource.name: Enrollment PCP Zip On Enrollment
resource.description: Original primary care physician (PCP) zip code as reporting on the eligibility record

resource.name: Enrollment Type
resource.description: Code for the type of enrollment

resource.name: Episode Admit Count
resource.description: Number of admissions related to the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Allowed Amount Outpatient (USD)
resource.description: Allowed amount for an out-patient episode, in USD

resource.name: Episode Allowed Amount PCP (USD)
resource.description: Allowed amount per episide for the primary care physician, in USD

resource.name: Episode Allowed Amount Primary Physician (USD)
resource.description: Allowed amount per episide for the primary physician, in USD

resource.name: Episode Allowed Amount Rx (USD)
resource.description: Allowed amount per episode for the medications, in USD

resource.name: Episode Allowed Amount Total (USD)
resource.description: Total allowed amount per episode, in USD

resource.name: Episode Body System
resource.description: Body system related to the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Cost Scale
resource.description: Cost scale of the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Derived Code
resource.description: Derived code for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Derived Indicator
resource.description: Derived indicator for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Disease Stage Code
resource.description: Disease stage code for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Duration (Days)
resource.description: Duration of the episode of care, specified in days

resource.name: Episode Group Code
resource.description: Group code for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Primary Physician
resource.description: Primary physician associated with the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Procedure Type Code
resource.description: Primary procedure type AHRQ code for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Rx Count
resource.description: Count of medications for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Summary Group Code
resource.description: Summary group code for the episode of care

resource.name: Episode Use Scale
resource.description: Use scale for the episode of care

resource.name: Ethnicity Code
resource.description: Code for the ethnicity of the person

resource.name: Evaluated Ouptut
resource.description: Attachment for content created as output when producing the insight.

resource.name: Exchange Plan Indicator
resource.description: Indicator that identifies if the plan is available on a healthcare exchange marketplace

resource.name: FFV Schedule
resource.description: Schedule code for the FFV initiative

resource.name: Family Id
resource.description: The unique identifier for the subscriber (contract holder, employee) and the associated dependents

resource.name: Family Income Level
resource.description: Code for the family income level of the person based on the Federal Poverty Level (FPL)

resource.name: Financial System
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the financial system

resource.name: Fully Insured Indicator
resource.description: Indicates whether the claim was for a fully insured plan

resource.name: Funding Arrangement
resource.description: Code for the funding arrangement

resource.name: Hierarchy Version Date
resource.description: Version date of the organinzational hierarchy represented

resource.name: Hierarchy VersionId
resource.description: Numeric version of the organinzational hierarchy represented

resource.name: Identified Pronouns
resource.description: Gender, typically described in terms of masculinity and femininity, is a social construction that varies across different cultures and over time.  This value is often used for identity purposes and should be collected directly from the patient.

resource.name: Immigration Status
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the immigration status of the person

resource.name: Industry Classification
resource.description: Industry classification code which can be based on the North American Industry Classification System (NAICS)

resource.name: Ingestion Batch Id
resource.description: The ID generated by an ingestion service. This represents a producer-submitted message collection

resource.name: Insight
resource.description: Element level insights relating to the element values in the contained resource instance

resource.name: Based On Value
resource.description: Value the insight result used as input

resource.name: Insight Confidence Details
resource.description: Insight Confidence Details

resource.name: Insight Detail
resource.description: The break down of information referenced to produce the insight and information specific scoring breakdown and output when appropriate

resource.name: Insight Id
resource.description: ID for the insight as it is known by the source (or source system) that this insight was provided from

resource.name: Insight Reference
resource.description: Reference to content leveraged to produce the insight.

resource.name: Insight Result
resource.description: Value specific insight result details

resource.name: Insight Result Summary
resource.description: Value specific final insight results

resource.name: Insight Score
resource.description: Score result produced by the scoring method for a specific insight

resource.name: Insight Summary
resource.description: Summarizes the insight associated with the element that the insight summary extension is embedded in. The insight array element in the meta section of the resource with the same insight record id contains the full details on the insight.

resource.name: Insight Type
resource.description: Code for the specific insight type.

resource.name: Insight Value
resource.description: Field value that this insight result pertains to.

resource.name: Insured
resource.description: Container for elements providing insurance context

resource.name: Insured Category
resource.description: Category of insurance

resource.name: Insured Rank
resource.description: Ordered rank to associate with an insurance option within a particular context (such as an Encounter)

resource.name: Job Class Code
resource.description: Classifcation group of the job role of the employee, for example, Top Executives, Post-secondary teachers, and Engineers

resource.name: Job Location Zipcode
resource.description: 5-digit zip code of the facility where the employee works

resource.name: Language Rank
resource.description: Specify preferred order of language use (1 = highest)

resource.name: Last Claim Indicator
resource.description: Indicates whether this claim record is the last or most recent claim

resource.name: Latitude
resource.description: Latitude for the address

resource.name: Legally Documented Sex
resource.description: Sex as defined or amended on the patient's legal documentation, for example a birth certificate or driver's license

resource.name: Level Of Care
resource.description: Code for the level of care

resource.name: Line Of Business
resource.description: Code for the line of business

resource.name: Local Number Of Units Per Service
resource.description: Customer-specific quantity of either services or units

resource.name: Local Race Code
resource.description: Customer-specific code for the race of the person

resource.name: Long Term Disability Benefit Rate
resource.description: Long term disability (LTD) benefit rate, expressed as a percentage of base wages (for example, 50.00%, 60.00%, 70.00%)

resource.name: Longitude
resource.description: Longitude for the address

resource.name: Longterm Care Duration
resource.description: Number of weeks for which the employee is eligible for long-term disability (LTD) benefits

resource.name: Longterm Care Waiting Period
resource.description: Elimination or waiting period for the long-term disability (LTD) benefit (for example, 90, 180 or 365 days). This is the amount of time between the first absent date and the coverage begin date.

resource.name: Major Diagnostic Category
resource.description: Body system or disease related groupings of clinical conditions, based on diagnosis codes

resource.name: Match Compared To
resource.description: Reference to the record that was compared for matching

resource.name: Match Confidence Code
resource.description: Confidence code for the match

resource.name: Confidence Score
resource.description: Confidence score for the match

resource.name: Match Criteria
resource.description: Criteria or algorythm used to identify the matched resource

resource.name: Match Detail
resource.description: Detailed match algorthm results used to match resources

resource.name: Match Method
resource.description: Method used to identify the matched resource

resource.name: Match Period
resource.description: Time period when match is valid

resource.name: MatchSourceReference
resource.description: Reference to the source resource that is matched

resource.name: Measure Parameter
resource.description: Defined parameter options implemented by the measure

resource.name: MeasureParameterValue
resource.description: Measure parameter value used to generate the measure report

resource.name: Measure Population Id
resource.description: Unique static identifier for the measure population that does not change between cohort engine runs. This is a user-friendly textual key (internal use only) that identifies a specific population. This id should be unique across all measures and should not change when a measure is versioned or when overrides are applied.

resource.name: Measure Report Assigned Practitioner
resource.description: The provider identifier of the physician(s) assigned to the rule measure using one of the physician attribution methods

resource.name: Measure Report Evidence
resource.description: Supporting evidence showing detailed data about why a patient qualified (or did not qualify) for measure rules

resource.name: Measure Report Evidence Population Id
resource.description: Population id of populations that reference or utilize the rule definition

resource.name: Measure Report Evidence Text
resource.description: Textual title or description of the rule definition within a measure report

resource.name: Measure Report Evidence Value
resource.description: Output value of rule definition within a measure report

resource.name: Measure Weight
resource.description: Measure Weight

resource.name: Medical Fully Insured Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of the fully insured medical coverage for the member or employee

resource.name: Medicare Coverage
resource.description: Standard code for the type of Medicare coverage, if any, for the person

resource.name: Medicare Indicator
resource.description: Indicator of Medicare coverage for the member

resource.name: Member Employee Indicator
resource.description: Code indicates whether the member is either an employee of the health plan, or the dependent of an employee of the health plan

resource.name: Network Id
resource.description: Customer-specific identifier of the patient provider network in which the member is enrolled

resource.name: Nonstandard Language
resource.description: Code for the language of the person

resource.name: Number of Units Allowed
resource.description: Customer-specific quantity of services or units allowed

resource.name: Nursing Home Indicator
resource.description: Indicates whether the claim was for a nursing home patient

resource.name: Offset Begin
resource.description: Offset location of the first character for the span of covered text in relation to the overall reference where this span of text appears

resource.name: Offset End
resource.description: Offset location of the last character for the span of covered text in relation to the overall reference where this span of text appears

resource.name: Parameter Value
resource.description: Value that was used for the parameter
